{"title_page": "Bad Child", "text_new": "{{short description|Song by Australian singer Toni Watson}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bad Child\n| cover      = Tones and I - Bad Child.png\n| caption    = Double A-side cover\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Tones and I]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{start date|2020|3|12|df=yes}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!--Please source genres-->\n| length     = 3:41\n| label      = Bad Batch\n| writer     = [[Tones and I|Toni Watson]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Konstantin Kersting]]|Watson}}\n| prev_title = [[The Kids Are Coming (song)|The Kids Are Coming]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| title      =\n| title2     = Can't Be Happy All the Time\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|e7cqIOF4_8s|\"Bad Child\"}}|header=Lyric video|type=single}}\n}}\n\"'''Bad Child'''\" is a song by Australian singer Toni Watson, known professionally as [[Tones and I]]. It was released on 12 March 2020 through Bad Batch alongside the song \"Can't Be Happy All the Time\". The double A-side single marks the first of more releases throughout the year, as announced by Watson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://au.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/tones-and-i-singles-bad-child-cant-be-happy-all-the-time-8422/|title=Tones And I Releases New Singles \"Bad Child\" and \"Can't Be Happy All the Time\"|last=Jenke|first=Tyler|website=[[Rolling Stone Australia]]|date=12 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOn 11 March 2020, Watson announced that there would be new music coming the next day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/tonesandimusic/status/1237522740975792128|title=New music coming tomorrow.... Camera with flash by Giulia McGauran|via=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> The song's release, along with \"Can't Be Happy All the Time\", was accompanied by an animated lyric video. The singer revealed that, for the first time, she has written a song \"in someone else's shoes; writing from their perspective\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/tones-and-i-shares-two-new-singles-2623909|title=Tones And I shares two new singles|last=Rose|first=Anna|website=[[NME (magazine)|NME]]|date=12 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> She further explained that the song is about \"seeing life growing up through someone else's eyes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://musicfeeds.com.au/news/tones-and-i-has-released-two-new-singles/|title=Tones And I Has Released Two New Singles|last=English|first=Laura|website=[[Music Feeds]]|date=12 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nAccording to Debbie Carr of [[Triple J]], the song was a trademark Tones and I song with Watson's \"fingerprints all over it\" and compared the lyrical context to \"[[Johnny Run Away]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/tones-and-i-comeback-bad-child-cant-be-happy-new-music-return/12046818|title=Tones and I releases first new music since debut EP|last=Carr|first=Debbie|website=[[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC (Australia)]]|date=12 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> On the other hand, Lars Brandle at ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' thought the track with its \"punchy keys and fat bass, all sitting under Tones' powerhouse vocals\" was reminiscent of Watson's previous hit \"[[Dance Monkey]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9333285/tones-and-i-bad-child-cant-be-happy-all-the-time-listen|title=Tones And I Returns With \"Bad Child\" and \"Can\u2019t Be Happy All The Time\": Listen|last=Brandle|first=Lars|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=12 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> ''[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'''s Mike Wass called the song a \"bop\" and predicted it to be \"all over radio in a couple of months\". Based on the song title, he described the song to be \"introspective and tinged with sadness\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7907910/tones-and-i-drops-new-songs-bad-child-you-cant-be-happy-all-the-time|title=Tones And I Drops New Songs \"Bad Child\" & \"You Can't Be Happy All The Time\"|last=Wass|first=Mike|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=12 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = Toni Watson\n| title1 = Bad Child\n| length1 = 3:41\n| title2 = Can't Be Happy All the Time\n| length2 = 4:16\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/132517594/credits|title=Bad Child/Can't Be Happy All the Time / Tones and I \u2013 Tidal|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[Tones and I|Toni Watson]] \u2013 songwriting, co-production\n* [[Konstantin Kersting]] \u2013 co-production, mixing\n* Andrei Eremin \u2013 mastering\n* Randy Belculfine \u2013 recording\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=30 March 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 16\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4836|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=23 March 2020|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Norway ([[VG-lista]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vglista.no/topplister/topp-20-single-2020-14/|title=VG-lista \u2013 Topp 20 Single uke 14, 2020|publisher=[[VG-lista]]|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 13\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Sweden ([[Sverigetopplistan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/41?dspy=2020&dspp=12|title=Veckolista Singlar, vecka 12|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 79\n|-\n{{single chart|Switzerland|73|artist=Tones and I|album=Bad Child|rowheader=true|accessdate=23 March 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Tones and I}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Tones and I songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Konstantin Kersting]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Song by Australian singer Toni Watson}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bad Child\n| cover      = Tones and I - Bad Child.png\n| caption    = Double A-side cover\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Tones and I]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{start date|2020|3|12|df=yes}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!--Please source genres-->\n| length     = 3:41\n| label      = Bad Batch\n| writer     = [[Tones and I|Toni Watson]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Konstantin Kersting]]|Watson}}\n| prev_title = [[The Kids Are Coming (song)|The Kids Are Coming]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| title      =\n| title2     = Can't Be Happy All the Time\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|1={{YouTube|e7cqIOF4_8s|\"Bad Child\"}}|header=Lyric video|type=single}}\n}}\n\"'''Bad Child'''\" is a song by Australian singer Toni Watson, known professionally as [[Tones and I]]. It was released on 12 March 2020 through Bad Batch alongside the song \"Can't Be Happy All the Time\". The double A-side single marks the first of more releases throughout the year, as announced by Watson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://au.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/tones-and-i-singles-bad-child-cant-be-happy-all-the-time-8422/|title=Tones And I Releases New Singles \"Bad Child\" and \"Can't Be Happy All the Time\"|last=Jenke|first=Tyler|website=[